Step 1 : Install VirtualBox using the following link : https://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads

Step 2 : Install Ubuntu using the following link : https://ubuntu.com/download/desktop

Step 3 : Go ahead and download VirtualBox and open Ubuntu in VirtualBox by giving an appropriate path and allocating enough space to it.

Step 4 : After opening the Ubuntu, Right click on the desktop and click on "Open Terminal".

Step 5 : After opening the terminal follow this link's " https://github.com/kunalg123/vsdflow " README file in order to download the packages.

Step 6 : Once done with the installation check if all the OpenSource Tools are succesfully installed or not. The snapshots for which will be shared in pdf format for sample reference.

For reference you may want to refer the free Udemy course for EDA Tools Installation : https://www.udemy.com/course/vsd-a-complete-guide-to-install-open-source-eda-tools/
                                                   And,for OpenLane and Sky130nm PDK : https://www.udemy.com/share/103wqE2@FG1jV0tKS1UGdU9GB3Zxfj1tSlRiYw==/
